Have you listened to the latest #DearGabbyPoecast Big Talk with @jennadewan 🦋Tune in to Dear Gabby #16 at the link in bio @gabbybernstein and learn ...

> How to speak to your children to avoid codependent relationships
> The importance of not making your feelings your children’s problem
> The struggles of finding balance as a working parent
> How dance kept Jenna embodied and healed her trauma
> Ways to gain confidence in your body through movement and sexuality
> Methods to physically process and move shame through you
> Why it’s essential to help our daughters feel confident in their bodies
> The secret to shame-free parenting

Click the link in my bio @gabbybernstein or search for "Dear Gabby" anywhere podcasts are streamed.

#jennadewan #deargabby #gracefullyyou #connection #happiness #workingparents #shamefree #noshame #parenting #boundaries #selflove #spiritjunkie

In this week's episode of Dear Gabby I teach one of the fastest ways to let go of control. It’s an old Dear Gabby method from 2006! 

This OG method is called the 3 Rs and it’s designed to help you rapidly process and release uncomfortable feelings in 90 seconds! 

The 3 Rs stands for Recognize, Record, Release.

It’s simple. All you need is to have a small journal on hand throughout the day. (Or you can use the Notes app in your iPhone.)

The next time you notice a negative controlling thought come up, do this:

Recognize: Notice the thought.
Record: Write it down in a journal.
Release: Say a prayer, “Thank you, Universe, for transforming this fear and helping me release it now.”

On the podcast I break this method down even further. (Link in bio)
